This only copies on odd rows when `scale_h` is true. But what about even rows? They are not copied at all? That would leave the output row uninitialized. That's a bug. Also, when `scale_h` is false, this branch does nothing (since the condition `gdv->scale_h && (y & 1)` would be false). But if `scale_h` is false and `scale_v` is false, we are in the first case (`!scale_v && !scale_h`), so that's okay. But if `scale_h` is false and `scale_v` is true? That case is handled in the else branch of the optimized code.

Wait, the optimized code's condition is:
